	(text_box "Note:\n\nESP32-S3-WROOM-1 Module\n\n• ESP32-S3 has four strapping pins:\n  GPIO0, GPIO3, GPIO45 and GPIO46.\n\n• GPIO0 is used for boot mode selection.\n  Keep pulled HIGH during normal operation.\n\n• GPIO3 is floating by default.\n\n• GPIO45 and GPIO46 are strapping pins and should\n  not be driven during reset.\n\n• USB Native Interface:\n  GPIO20 = USB_D+\n  GPIO19 = USB_D-\n\n• EN pin must be pulled up to 3.3V through a 10kΩ resistor.\n\n• Place 100nF decoupling capacitors close to the 3V3 pins.\n\n• Keep copper, traces and components away from the\n  PCB antenna area of the module.\n\n• Verify GPIO usage against the latest Espressif\n  datasheet before final PCB manufacturing."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 156.21 97.79 0)
		(size 38.1 36.83)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
